nuspell
------------------------------------------
Nuspell is a spell checker library and command-line program designed for
languages with rich morphology and complex word compounding. Nuspell is a pure
C++ re-implementation of Hunspell.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.7-1
  libboost_locale1.66-1.66.0-1
  libgcc1-10.2.0-1
  libicu-devel-68.1-1
  libicu68-68.1-1
  libnuspell-devel-4.1.0-1bl1
  libnuspell4-4.1.0-1bl1
  libstdc++6-10.2.0-1
  pkg-config-1.6.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.34+1git.de9c1b7cfe-1
  cmake-3.17.3-2
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-10.2.0-1
  gcc-g++-10.2.0-1
  gcc-objc-10.2.0-1
  gcc-objc++-10.2.0-1
  ninja-1.10.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/nuspell/nuspell

Canonical download:
  git://github.com/nuspell/nuspell.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack nuspell-4.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./nuspell-4.1.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/nuspell-4.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/nuspell-4.1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libnuspell4-4.1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libnuspell-devel-4.1.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(nuspell)
  /usr/bin/nuspell.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/nuspell.README
  /usr/share/doc/nuspell/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/nuspell/CHANGELOG.md
  /usr/share/doc/nuspell/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/nuspell/COPYING.LESSER
  /usr/share/doc/nuspell/README.md

(libnuspell4)
  /usr/bin/cygnuspell-4.dll

(libnuspell-devel)
  /usr/include/nuspell/aff_data.hxx
  /usr/include/nuspell/dictionary.hxx
  /usr/include/nuspell/finder.hxx
  /usr/include/nuspell/nuspell_export.h
  /usr/include/nuspell/structures.hxx
  /usr/lib/cmake/nuspell/NuspellConfig.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/nuspell/NuspellConfigVersion.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/nuspell/NuspellTargets-release.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/nuspell/NuspellTargets.cmake
  /usr/lib/libnuspell.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/nuspell.pc

